<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-216-390  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 216 390.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  Feb 12 1990 v29 n4 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Data Translation drops prices, extends warranty.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Andrews, Warren.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Data Translation drops the prices of many of its data acquisition,image processing and array processing board-level products by asmuch as 50 percent in reaction to increased competition; thecompany's new product warranty is being extended from 90 days toone year as well, and new service and support mechanisms are beingenacted.andP;  The actions follow by six months an earlier round ofprice cutting that accompanied a layoff of almost 20 percent ofthe company's workforce.andP;  Data Translation has focused in recentyears on its image processing products, primarilyMacintosh-compatible frame grabbers and image enhancement boardsused in desktop publishing.andP;  Some analysts claim the company mayhave hurt its data acquisition board efforts as a result of itsemphasis on image processing products.andP;  Data Translation'sstrategy for success in an increasingly competitive market isdiscussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Data Translation Inc. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    DATX.andO;Topic:     Image ProcessingGraphics Boards-CardsData Acquisition SystemsManufacturersMarketing StrategyPrice CuttingFinancial StabilityWarranty.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>